subject: Rajasthan History
question_en: Which king is associated with the construction of Udaipur?
question_hi: उदयपुर के निर्माण के लिए कौन सा जीवनकालीन कहाने का प्रभावी है।
explanation_en: Rana Kumbha is known to have played a significant role in the construction of Udaipur, also known as the City of Lakes (बीजलों का मंदिर)
explanation_hi: राने कुम्ब एक उच्चारखण्डरहस्ताने संगम एन्टर के देश का अर्थांतरहस्ता के विभंग
D_explanation: Rana Kumbha, one of the prominent rulers of Mewar, is known for his contribution in the construction of Udaipur, the city established by Rana Kumbha's descendant Rana Sangram Singh.

D_explanation: Rana Kumbha, a prominent ruler of Mewar, established the city of Udaipur. Udaipur was founded by Rana Kumbha's descendant, Rana Sangram Singh.

D_explanation: Raja Rao Jaisal Singh, who was a descendant of Rana Kumbha, founded the city of Jaisalmer.
